<HH> ============= Screen: Fidelity info ======================== </HH>

<IntakeGate ready="!@fba3_completion_checkbox.value">
<Markdown> </Markdown>
<Markdown id="fba3_fidelity_info">
## Implementation Fidelity

Implementation fidelity refers to how accurately and consistently a behavior plan is implemented as it was designed. There are five key aspects:

1. **Adherence** — Are all steps of the plan followed as written?
2. **Dosage** — Is the plan used for the correct amount of time/frequency?
3. **Quality of Delivery** — Are the strategies implemented correctly and with the intended tone/approach (e.g., calm redirection vs. yelling)?
4. **Participant Responsiveness** — Is the child actually exposed to and engaged with the intervention?
5. **Program Differentiation** — Are other strategies (not part of the plan) avoided during implementation?
</Markdown>
</IntakeGate>


<HH> ============= Screen: Fidelity tabs ======================== </HH>

<IntakeGate ready="!@fba3_completion_checkbox.value">
<Markdown> </Markdown>
<Tabs id="fba3_fidelity_tabs">
<Vertical id="fba3_fidelity_tab1" title="Fidelity Overview">
<Markdown>
## Five Aspects of Implementation Fidelity

| Aspect | Key Question |
|--------|-------------|
| **Adherence**                | Are all steps of the plan followed as written?                                        |
| **Dosage**                   | Is the plan used for the correct amount of time/frequency?                            |
| **Quality of Delivery**      | Are strategies implemented correctly and with the intended tone?                       |
| **Participant Responsiveness** | Is the child actually exposed to and engaged with the intervention?                 |
| **Program Differentiation**  | Are other strategies (not part of the plan) avoided during implementation?             |
</Markdown>
</Vertical>
<Vertical id="fba3_fidelity_tab2" title="Modifications &amp; Checklist">
<Markdown>
## When Fidelity Is Low

When the person implementing the plan is not following it accurately, you can:

- **Simplify** the plan so it's easier to follow
- **Provide training** on each step
- **Create checklists** to track whether each step was completed
- **Offer coaching** and feedback after each session
- **Set reminders** to prompt specific actions

A **fidelity checklist** is a simple tool that lists each step of the plan with a yes/no checkbox, so the implementer can track whether they completed each step during each session.
</Markdown>
</Vertical>
</Tabs>
</IntakeGate>


<HH> ============= Screen: Fidelity check ====================== </HH>

<Vertical id="fba3_fidelity_check">
<Markdown>
## Comprehension Check

Annie's roommate said:
- She sometimes forgets to do the warning countdown and timer
- She forgets the small bedtime reward
- She often falls into negotiating or arguing when he whines for extended time
</Markdown>

<MarkupProblem id="fba3_fidelity_choice" title="Fidelity Area"><![CDATA[
>>Which is the main area of treatment fidelity that Annie's roommate is struggling with?<<

(x) Adherence
( ) Dosage
( ) Quality of delivery
( ) Participant responsiveness
( ) Program differentiation

[explanation]
The main issue is **adherence** — Annie's roommate is not following all the steps of the plan as written. She forgets the countdown timer, forgets the bedtime reward, and falls into negotiating instead of ignoring escape behaviors. These are all failures to adhere to the specific steps in the intervention plan.
[/explanation]
]]></MarkupProblem>
</Vertical>


