<Markdown id="fba3_updated_plan">
## Updated Behavior Modification Plan

TODO: This should display the original escape-focused plan from Part 5 with the student's selected modifications incorporated. Ideally, the modifications the student selected above would be inserted into the appropriate sections of the plan.

For now, here is the updated plan with all possible modifications noted:

**Original Antecedent Strategies:**
- Create a predictable bedtime routine with a visual schedule
- Use a timer to signal when each routine step begins and ends
- Give 10-minute and 5-minute advance warnings
- Incorporate a brief preferred activity into the routine
- Allow limited choices within the routine

**Original Consequence Strategies:**
- Provide positive reinforcement (sticker chart, praise) for on-time bedtime
- Ignore escape behaviors — do not chase or engage
- Use a "bedtime pass" for one approved brief delay per night
- Provide brief positive attention when Johnny stays in bed

**New Adherence Supports:**
- Step-by-step guide posted where the roommate can see it
- Fidelity checklist to mark off each step during each session
- Phone reminders for key transition points
- Weekly check-in with Annie to review and troubleshoot

**Data Collection:**
- Continue tracking bedtime compliance for 2 more weeks
- Use fidelity checklist to track plan adherence each session
</Markdown>
</IntakeGate>


